&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Would you like the opportunity to support senior decision makers to meet the growing health and social care needs in our communities? Do you have a keen eye for detail? Do you want to work in an appreciative and supportive team where you&#39;ll have an opportunity to develop?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to support the Divisional Senior Management Team in Community Services Division. Based at Newcourt House with good transport links to the M5/City Centre, you will have the opportunity to extend your experience to provide first class administrative support to senior managers as well a chance for professional and personal development in a warm and welcoming team of 4 PAs. We&#39;re keen to hear from you if you are a proactive individual who can work both in a team and autonomously, whilst maintaining confidentiality and a professional manner.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our vision is to provide safe, high quality seamless services delivered with courtesy and respect. To achieve our vision we expect all our staff to uphold our Trust values. Our Trust values are:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Honesty, Openness &amp; Integrity&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Fairness, Inclusion &amp; Collaboration&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Respect &amp; Dignity&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
